caption: One of the better sandwich/soup chains in Indianapolis. This store is located on the downtown circle and is usually not crowded for being in a high traffic area . The sandwiches and ingredients are fresh. Staff is polite and quick to get your order to you. The place is clean and nicely kept.
Awesome sandwiches

This is a popular place on The Circle and is usually a good choice for lunch.  They have been going through a lot of new staff lately, though, and the quality of the effort is sometimes not what I'm sure the franchise owner would want.  The "Wreck" sandwich is usually great.  Update:  Had to bump the rating down a bit.  As has always been the case, this restaurant really struggles when they're busy.  Hasn't been a problem for a long time (since the downtown office workers all left) but it showed up again this past week during the Big Ten Tourney.  Rude employees, poor quality control on orders.  If you're going to go here, do so when they're not busy.
Was very happy with my first experience.
Customer Service was great and my food was ready at the time they said it would be when i placed my order online.  I definitely recommend going here when you are in the Circle downtown.

Potbelly Sandwich Shop is located right on Monument circle in downtown Indy on the East side which makes it very close to everyone. When you first walk in you feel like you are transported to a small NY eatery. The aroma of cooking meat waif's thru the air and you are met with a line of people. The place does have some seating even though it is small. The food counter is typical of most places and runs the length. You place your order and wait for them to prepare it. It can be somewhat loud. There are quite a lot of sandwich and soup pairrings. This is not your typical Subway food. The meat is excellent and so is the bread. Portions are good and the sandwich's come out quite hot. I like to walk over with a coworker and grab a sandwich to take back to the office. I definitely recommend adding this to your regular lunch routine.

Called the restaurant because there was a problem with my order.  We ordered two bigs. One wreck and one turkey and ham.  I had the turkey and added ham. We were supposed to have extra meat,  bacon and cheese.  The sandwich had no cheese at all, no ham and no bacon.  The manager called me a liar by telling me that she specifically made the sandwiches and she knows that she put those items on there. What would I possibly gain by lying about that? Did I pick the items off just to mess with her head? Will never order from there again. Picture is attached.  You be the judge! Anyone see any ham? Cheese? Bacon?
Super friendly, attentive, great service and sandwiches.
Nice hot sandwiches! I recommend ordering ahead if you're ordering for lunch during the week.
Quiet,  fast,  and delicious!!
I love this place. They make amazing, hot sandwiches.
I got a potbelly eatin my pot belly. yummy, yummy, love in my tummy

I think it is a good place to pick up your food, but not really nice to eat in. The place is very small and I have the feeling that it is not clean that often, specially the restrooms. Nevertheless, the food tastes good and the staff is very friendly. Do not expect much difference if you compare it to McAlisters or Panera Bread.
Grat as always
Different treatments for different folks pretty much discrimination in that place.
Great lunch stop.
Delicious food. Lots of options for bread with sandwiches. Many toppings options and healthy choices.

Very delicious sandwich. Ordered from door-dash & they ran out of broccoli cheddar soup (probably because it is good as well) - refunded me for the soup and still gave me a surprise chicken pot pie soup instead on the house with a little note. Very nice, Thank you!

Had never had this place before so I thought I'd try it. Got delivery. Put in order for the 3:00 time slot and did not get my food until 3:30. Which fine, things happen. Traffic or what have you. But I did not get a call or notification that the deliver would be running behind. I ordered a 20oz bottle of coke but got a 16oz can of diet. Yuck! And my jaw is literally sore from eating the Wreck. Tasted great but the bread was burnt and super hard. The sandwich was also not even warm.i will probably try it again and give a second chance but not too thrilled with first experience.
Very good sandwiches
Get the chilli peppers on your sandwich!
Baked deliciousness in every bite.  Seriously, just try it
I work on the circle and this place is always fast and convenient. And the sandwiches are pretty good I recommend ordering online if you have short lunch break makes it so much easier.
Delicious food.
Nice staff and great sandwiches but the bathroom was unavailable.
Best sandwiches and soup ever!!
Hands down my most visited lunch spot. Same price a Jimmy or subway but 3x as good
CHILI & HOT PRIME RIB SANDWICHES... WONDERFUL!!!!!!
The service was very good, and so were the 2 guys who helped us with our order
Great sandwiches always busy
Best downtown Indy sandwiches period!
Great food, heavenly Mac and cheese, and amazing service.

Always a great staff, and quick to get your order put together. Tasty sandwiches with plenty of topping options, and several choices for chips & drinks. If you can navigate the homeless population on the circle, you'll have a great meal from Potbelly's!
Conveniently located at the circle Great tasting food Staff was friendly Would def be eating here again
Delicious ssndwiches

I had always heard great things about potbelly's, but maybe it's location based. The service was great, but the food was utterly disappointing. So bland and just had such a generic sandwich chain composition. All the food had a texture as if it were pre-prepared long before I had ever even considered trying potbelly's. I certainly didn't enjoy my overall experience, but if someone I'm with wants to go to potbelly's, I might give it another shot. I'm a glutton for punishment, and again the service was great.
This place is the bomb!!!! Love the Big Wreck all the time!! Excellent place!!
Mediterranean sandwich excellent

This is a pretty standard sandwich place that toasts your sandwich in a toaster and let's you pick your toppings after you've chosen the meat of the sandwich. My grilled chicken was very filling, but the Chips were so so. In a sandwich place, I always expect some form of kettle cooked chips because those fit the best for me! Maybe having chips come on a plate with the sandwich might be better off for presentation. Overall, the meal hit the spot but it was nothing to go out of your way to try when you stop downtown.
1rst timer......DELISH!!!!!!!!!!!

The food is good, but be wary of online ordering at this location. More often than not it is late, so plan accordingly when it's your lunch break. Also, my orders have not always been correct. Staff could also be friendlier during lunch.
Excellent soup and sandwiches
Get the Wreck if you like a little heat.
The food and service are both excellent but the space is too small for the crush of a lunch crowd.
Love love love the food! Soup & sandwich..yes!
Great sandwich, quick service
Always a great shop

My team decided to do a pitch in from here, and I got the Vegetarian sub, which sounded amazing. Only cheese I see on the sub is Cheddar, no mayo to be seen, there were more mushrooms than anything on the sandwich and those had a strange taste to them so I picked them off. What I was left with was two small tomato slices, a small sprinkle of lettuce, and bread. Pretty disappointed. Never had Potbelly's food before, and don't think I'll be re-ordering anything anytime soon.
Great place
Over priced

Their sandwiches are always too dry. My coworkers rave about this place, but I have yet to have a sandwich from them that has impressed me. Their soups are quite good, but overpriced. Also, the interior of the restaurant always smells like smoke, as if bread crumbs are burning in the oven. This is a problem other sandwich chains have solved, but it is constant here. I work upstairs in the same building, and about the only time I come here is if I'm desperate because it's pouring down rain and I forgot my umbrella.
The floor was filthy dirty.  Looked it has not been moped properly in weeks if not months.  The tables were  sticky.  The place was a nasty dump.
Really good sandwiches and salads. The Mixed Berry smoothie was very refreshing on a muggy summer day.
Good sandwich.
Good sandwiches tasty.
Superfast service and great hot sandwiches!
nice little shop.

Fast and friendly service, the dining area was a bit dirty given the time we were there (around 8pm, and it wasn't busy), but it wasn't the worst place I've ever seen. The food is good, especially the chicken pot pie soup.
Love love love it!
Great food and friendly staff
It was amazing
Decent sandwich. Broccoli Cheddar soup needed something, it wasn't great.

Great casual vegetarian sandwhich. Not explicitly printed on the menu but ask for "the veggie/the vegetarian" sandwhich and you'll get an option of bread and by default it comes with three cheeses and mushrooms. Oven roasted and then you pick cold veggies subway style. Avocado is extra.  Wonderful place to grab a faster sitdownish sandwich. Do not be dissuaded by a long line. They bust out a tablet and start taking orders down that line and those sandwhich start firing out of that kitchen.  Vegetarians be warned - when this place gets cooking you will be treated to an overwhelming, thick cloud of meat smells.  To avoid either of these situations stay away from  the 9-5er downtown lunch rush.
Great food, smells are delightful, service was quick
Got the pick 2 pair. I got the meatball sandwich and powerhouse salad. The salad was pretty good. Sand which was good too but nothing special
Food is great but the restrooms are disgusting...
Excellent food. Had very good service.
Excellent Mac and Cheese
Great sandwiches & soup
Excellent sandwiches.

Came here with my girlfriend and we each got the pick two. Portion sizes were small, but the food was tasty. The employees wouldn’t speak loud enough to be heard so it was hard to know what to order. Good location with a good view though.
Love this place. So yummy!!
One of the best sandwich spots in the city.
Good food good people and always have the order right and ready if you order through mobile app is there even show you how to use the mobile app if you're unfamiliar on how to use it
username: bebzter at google mail dot com

caption: Worst experience ever, and it is still not over.  As I sit here starving and have had 5 phone calls with the store, I ponder in amazement how they could neither take my credit card number correctly or find my hotel right outside Lucas oil stadium.  Apparently this is rocket science.  I'm not normally a negative reviewer or name caller, but what I am experiencing is simply moronic.  Been working hard all Sunday and just want my food (very late and still not here). Mystified.  Update, order canceled.  On to jimmy johns.

I had the cheese steak and though it was okay, I did not consider it to be very flavorful. Not to say I would not eat there again, but I am not eager to return either. Will try a different sandwich next time.
Excellent food. Although my favorite thing on the menu is their malts.

Resisted coming here for about a year and a half because the name was gross to me, but I stumbled in about a week ago and can’t get enough. Amazing, fresh ingredients used in the salads, delicious dressings and filling portions for a very reasonable price. Great lunch spot!
Excellent food and employees.
Great sandwiches!! Milkshakes are the best in town!! There was a guy there named Dustin who was amazing!! He made my day!! Awesome service!!
Wonderful food! AND amazing service! Thank you Potbelly! 💓 Love the vintage theme as well!
Has good food. Some staff members are slightly rude. Oddly enough,  I've found this place happens to serve some of the best smoothies that you can find in Indianapolis
Had what was advertised as a philly...Good bread ....The meat reminded me of a Hot Pocket Philly .Mac and cheese was over cooked nastiness with bacon on top
Great food, amazing view and great staff. I love this place.
Better then subway
Good food, fast service and friendly staff.

Have been coming here and loving it since I started working downtown 7 years ago. However it is clearly under new management and has lost its mojo. Don't get me wrong, food still delicious. But.....empty chip display.... empty cookie display.. ... trash overflowing.... just not the same.
Serviceable. Quick. Fun fact: One of the suicide girls use to work here.

Even though there were less then 5 people sitting down eating....I felt rushed when ordering.Sandwich was not worth the price and staff was rude.Didn't even know the  online perk of the day.Had to pull up the email & show them.Won't go out of my way to go back

We recently moved into Circle Tower and have had a chance to try most of the restaurant offerings in/near our building.  We are now convinced that there are no really good options near The Circle but, of the ones that exist, Potbelly is one of the best.  Their staff often leaves a little to be desired in the hygiene dept. but that is par for the course downtown.  If you must eat something downtown, this is likely the best you'll find.
Locstion is great and Very delicious chicken and cheddar sandwishes with different toppings.
Better fresh made sandwiches you can get downtown than larger chains.
The food is fantastic and very reasonably priced and the staff are super friendly and funny.
They were passing out free sandwiches on the street!
I would suggest any sandwich from Potbelly but be prepared to wait for your food here because they are usually busy and understaffed. Overall, great, affordable place to grab a quick meal.

Your experience here will entirely depend on what time of day you visit.  When they're not busy, sandwiches are great and so is the service.  When they're busy?  Sandwiches are almost always poorly prepared, and not to order, and the service is poor as well.  If you want to eat here, don't go at busy lunch hours.
Quick to get your meal.  Good sandwhiches.
Love this place.   Staff is fantastic,  service is great, food is always excellent!!!!!
Great toasted subs!

Really good sandwiches. The Cuban was a great sandwich with good tasting pulled pork, though could have had a bit more pork. Also tried the turkey club, Pizza sandwich, and A Wreck. All were very filling and the bread was really good. Enjoyed the experience and the view.
Love Potbelly. Downtown has a nice environment.
Great food for a good price
Decent food for the price and the line always seems to move along nicely.

I think the management has been changed a while ago and since then quality of the sandwiches and the staff also was changed. never get the right order and always missing items that you wanna add or it is supposed be in the sandwich that you picked. Staff is look like they do not wanna work or listen you. Three stars are for still fresh baked multigrain bread and the ice cream shakes.

This location is a mess  and they never get the order right.  You ask for something additional and while they have no problem taking your money for it, they never put it in your order.  They never deliver your food on time.  I called today and they called and said they were out of potato salad.  Fine, substitute something else.  45 minutes later I called and my order has never left store.  So, 1 hour and 10 minutes after ordering, I still do not have my food.
Veggie options were sparse but still very tasty.

My favorite sub shop downtown! I go weekly. The last couple times I've gone, they were out of my usual but the other menu items I've tried are really good too! Cozy atmosphere. It is usually crowded at lunch time though and sometimes no seats available.
So good!!
Good sandwiches.  Friendly staff.  Like the Mac n cheese.  Recommend for a quick hot bite.
Mushroom Melt is awesome! Fast service
Great sandwiches
Good eats
A good place for sandwich lunch downtown Indy that has a great very busy but efficient blue collar vibe with plenty of great staff and service! A good place to sit down with a couple of friends!
Great food!
Chicken salad is made in house and tasted fresh.
Never heard of this restaurant, but happened to walk by it and decided to try it. Very good sandwiches!
Loved my sandwich got the Mushroom Melt  and the staff was super friendly.
Good food but verrrry smoky. Get some exhaust fans already.
The dinning area was a bit messy. The floor needed sweeping very badly. I had the pizza sandwich and it was delicious.
I saw a guy on a pogo stick while eating a delicious sandwich 5 out of 5 would recommend if I could see the pogo stick again.

I had never heard of Potbelly Sandwiches but I was down town  for a meeting and needed to go to the bank on the circle. I walked passed it, went to the bank and stopped in on the way back and was so glad I did. The sandwiches were wonderful, very good. Just wish the had Pepsi products!
Willing to go out of their way to fix a screwed up order.  Only complaint is the smell of the place.  The sandwiches are great.
Try whatever they recommend

Our office has placed multiple orders with Potbelly and, while our co-workers love the food, they have yet to arrive with the full order and/or the correct order.  Unfortunately, I believe today was their last chance and we will not be ordering from them again in the future. You would think that large orders with multiple items would be double-checked for accuracy so that they WOULD get return customers but I guess being downtown, they are busy enough that they do not care if they lose large customers.
Very nice sandwiches!
They are rude as hell to they're employees.When I was in there I heard a manager yes at a girl and made her cry.I honestly would never recommend this place.I hope that girl gets a better job.
Yummy, great staff
I'm not sure what the deal is with the "smoky" atmosphere every time I come here (maybe bad ventilation?) but the hot sandwiches are great.  Pizza sub is my goto.
Great customer service, food was prepared quickly.  Selection was good but not abundant. Quality was great.  The Mac and Cheese is tasty!
Very good love the pastrami and Italian
Awesome food
Good soup and sandwiches in an informal setting.
Decent sanwiches, but the space is too smokey, and your clothes will stink after a visit!
Great sandwiches, fast line.
Sucks

Always good food, wide choice of options. Friendly staff, helpful with descriptions. Can be very busy, but quality remains high. Only downside is that it can be hard to hear while ordering, as there's a lot of noise in the place.
Food is a 4/5 but they cannot seem to move at a devent pace getting orders made or in order.  The wait and slow pace in a location where speed is key docks their rating.
Everything you want in a toasty sub sandwich. Cozy atmosphere.
Great sandwiches!
Ask for extra peppers at the counter! Not many people know this!

I ordered online to have it delivered to the hospital while I was getting my staples removed. He called I told him entrance two, my driver went down shortly after to meet him and he rode away from entrance one. My driver tried yelling at him to get his attention, but to no avail. When we called 5 minutes later they told us the rider just got back and that wasn't in their delivery rage, though he was just there, so I asked for a refund and they told me that it will take a week for me to get my money back, which I don't have much of right now cause im crippled at the moment. I didn't get a notice or anything of a refund in my email, so I don't know if they're trying to steal my money, or if it actually takes them a week to refund. I missed lunch and my rehab has strict breakfast, lunch, and dinner times, so I don't get to eat today :( not happy with my service. Would never recommend this restaurant to anyone.
Great sandwich, but almost unbearable with the smoke from the oven to sit inside the restaurant.
Best sandwiches downtown!
Like subway but not as trashy.
Delicious sandwiches, came in at peak lunch time and they take the orders of the line via iPad. Brilliant. Fast and delicious. Cheers
Good food at a good price
Good food, good location!
Standard Potbelly's.
I love the Italian sub and the fact that they have vegan options for my kids.
Food is always hot and tasty. Friendly staff, quick service.
Food was great did not t enjoy being starred at by two employees while i was eating.
Good food
By far my favorite sandwich place!
Great food and atmosphere.  The salads are large enough to share and the toppings are great.  My fav is the Mediterranean salad with humus and peppers.
The sandwiches are delicious!
Great sandwich shop with great chili!
Love the Hot peppers, make sure you add them to your sandwich.
Always a treat and the service is always fast and friendly
Not realizing they weren't open yet I showed up ten minutes before opening and they still happily served me. Everyone was busy but they helped me anyways. A stand up staff!
I love this little sandwich place.
Normally love potbelly but the last four times they messed up the order.
That Mediterranean on Flat bread. .with chicken. .

I ordered the pizza sandwich, I got mine with double meat, delicious the staff was friendly and great service. The cookies are yummy! Plus where I sat at the window was an enjoyable view. I'll be back again!!
Turkey & bacon on regular bread, provolone, & veggies. Nothing to rave about, but ok. Customer service was ok/good.
Though this place has a lot of seating, it gets extremely busy. The food is good, but not great.
Awesome food
This is one of my FAVORITE places to go for HOAGIES! I always get the turkey with provolone.
Quick and clean.
great food, peppers are a must have! fun casual enviro!!
Usually good
Reliable service and great atmosphere.

Small-ish menu, but I've actually eaten 95% of the offerings and everything was good. There are a ton of things to look at and read in this place, and the staff behind the counter are very friendly. They have a couple of delivery bike guys who are snotty douche bags, though. They like to hang out outside and pat themselves on the back for being so awesome; they are hard to miss.
Great subs and an even friendlier staff!
The salad I had was very good

This is my favorite sub shop in Indianapolis. If you like sandwiches, you should definitely try this restaurant! By default the sandwiches are hot. The unique thing about Potbelly is that the hot sandwiches are not greasy! I usually get their Italian sub and it is not greasy at all. Their hot peppers are super good. All the ingredients are very fresh. This is a must try place!
Great sandwiches great staff my favorite is the young handsome muscular guy I think his name is John
Was fine but I do not think they have bathrooms.
Loved i pretty much get the same sandwich the wreck the bomb
Very good sandwiches. It's a nice hole in the wall sandwich shop. Very satisfied.
Friendly staff and great food!

Potbelly is my favorite downtown sub shop. It's a really cute location, with fast and friendly service. The subs are toasted and hot, piled up just the way you like it. The Potbelly peppers are the perfect topping for a little extra pizzazz. Extras include chips, jumbo pickles, cookies, and milk shakes.
Good sandwiches, but need to figure out the smoke problem. Not ventilated very well.
Great sandwiches and salads.
The wreck!
Great potbelly!  Line out the door clears in less than 5 minutes, just have faith!
Pretty standard sub sandwiches. Food we got was not bad, but a lot of menu options were sold out early in the evening.
Excellent sandwiches.
Great for a quick bite and chill. Good shakes and cookies for dessert.
Awesome little sandwich shop
Always a good experience here, even at lunch time. The staff are friendly and fast, the food is good. I just wish it was a little roomier.
Wreck with Mayo and hot peppers....and everything else ;)
It's not bad, but not great either. Maybe I caught them on an off day?
I am a sandwich fanatic. Love all sandwiches. Potbelly gave one of the best sandwiches I've ever had. Great place to grab a sandwich.
Great sandwiches. Fast, friendly service.
Great prices, great sandwiches, fast service
The food was great, but it was definitely busy. The line to order was out the door.
One of the best sandwiches on monument circle
Great subs
Love the wreck and the hot peppers!

This is what small sandwich shop in a big city should feel like! Classic vibe with lots of hustle and bustle, newspaper clippings and signs on the walls. It's usually really busy around lunch time, but that's because its a rather popular place. Sandwiches are delicious!
Amazing sandwiches for a great price!
Good sandwich place, pretty simple and quick.
Great sandwiches and shakes!
Cool atmosphere. Close to everything. Really good food!

What a lovely place! Decided to give this place a try after several people told me how great it was... and they weren't lying. The place itself is very unique and full of all sorts of stuff. Orders are taken on the far left side of the counter. After examining the menu I ordered. There were two people behind the counter, a guy and a girl. IDK if the girl was new, or just given a hard time by the guy, but either way the dynamic between the two was energetic and fun.  After our sandwiches made a pass through the toaster we added our toppings and went along with our day. Before selecting a seat outside (it was a beautiful fall day) we commented on how inexpensive our meal was. $17 for two people is amazing... especially when we are used to paying $25+ elsewhere. The food was absolutely delicious. Made me happy... and really that's what's important. Good flavor and great value!  The place itself is clean, bright (huge windows overlooking monument circle), and plenty of places to sit. They do have a small section outside to sit as well (clearly as it was mentioned above). They do offer other items than a sandwich, such as smoothies, soup, and I believe even salads. They do have some baked goods at the counter as well.  Its a great little place and I'm sure that I'll be back again.

Great sandwich and shake restaurant. Friendly staff and good service. My family frequently walks down to the circle on the weekend and has a sandwich and shake - the staff always accommodates our request to make a shake and split into two cups for the kids to share.  The sandwiches are excellent and can be custom ordered for non-menu items. The shakes are also very good.
Best sandwich place, hands down. You should go there. The staff is friendly and energetic. It's all around a great place. Oh, and try a smoothie.

Extreme bad service. Placed an order for delivery an hour and half back. I was told by the delivery guy that the order was placed only half an hour back according to the receipt. Called them twice but the response was cavalier. Wanted to buy from them for the rest of my week's stay in Indy but not sure anymore.
I have ate there several times and I love it. Recommend it to anyone in the area
Awesome food and shakes
Honestly one of the bust subs I've ever eaten

Pretty good place for sandwiches. I ordered ahead and my order was ready exactly on time. Only reason I'm knocking a star is because I feel that their meat portions are a bit lackluster. Good experience otherwise.
Great sandwich options and a huge variety of delicious combinations.  I love their chili, and the oatmeal cookies may be the best I have ever had!

We order from Potbelly a lot! The online system is so easy to use and order. I work near the restaurant and we have always had an on time delivery. I really like the quality of catering that they do for meetings too. It is presentable and delicious.
Best food and sandwiches in the downtown area. The owner and employees are great. Plus their chocolate brownie cookie is the best!

I was recently in Indianapolis for a conference with a group of hungry teens. I had been to the Potbelly Sandwich in Washington, DC so I knew what kind of food to expect for a cheap price. I tried the meatball sub and the seasonal peppermint milkshake. Both were very delicious. Everyone in the group I was with was able to find something that they would enjoy. We also had a gluten free vegetarian in the group and she was very happy with the selection and options that she had to choose from. The staff was very welcoming and one of the workers checked in on us throughout the meal to see how every one liked it. Definitely a great place to go for lunch and dinner. It is within walking distance of the convention center and Lucas Oil Stadium.
I absolutely love their pizza sandwich and Oreo milkshake it's the best! Great taste for such a cheap cost.

Looking for a lunch spot while walking downtown Indy and wanted something light, good, and a sandwich. This fit the bill perfect. Decent fresh sub's, nice decor, clean, fast, and good service. I got the wreck on wheat with mayo, lettuce, Italian seasoning, and potbelly vinaigrette. The sandwich wasn't as big as I've received at other sub's places, but it was just enough to fill me up. I really enjoyed it, and really enjoyed the potbelly vinaigrette. I gave it 4 stars because they don't have sweet tea just unsweetened. They need sweat tea :-)
Great food, great price and great service.

I always place my order online. I like that I can customize my sandwich just as if I was at the restaurant ordering. I can also save orders so when I am ordering for a monthly meeting at work I can just place the order not worry about it. I have never had any problems and the delivery is quick and efficient.

One afternoon my office was getting a little hungry we called Potbelly's to see if we cold have some cookies delivered. They said that they would have to bake them fresh so it would take a little bit of time, but they were delivered fresh and hot. The whole office appreciated the amazing customer service that this store offered us!

The chili is really tasty and the tuna sandwich is also really good. I've always ordered directly from my office and it is delivered in a timely fashion and well insulated to make sure it arrives intact.
This is the place you should eat, now!
They have good sandwiches and large salads.  They have a cozy space on the circle, if you can find a seat.
Good sandwiches, great atmosphere and good employees.
Just go there... the sandwiches do all the talking.(not literally)
